'''海栖热袍菌'''（[[學名|學名]]：''Thermotoga maritima''）是[[熱袍菌屬|熱袍菌屬]]的一種細菌，屬[[革蘭氏陰性|革蘭氏陰性]]的[[桿菌|桿菌]]<ref name="MSU"/>，生存在[[海底熱泉|海底熱泉]]中<ref>{{cite web |publisher=[[National_Center_for_Biotechnology_Information|National Center for Biotechnology Information]] |title=Hyperthermophilic organism that shows extensive horizontal gene transfer from archaea |work=BioProject |year=2003 |access-date=January 14, 2012 |url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/bioproject/111}}</ref>，最適生長溫度為攝氏80度，在55度至90度的水中皆可生長，為少數在高溫生長的細菌之一<ref name="Huber">{{cite journal | vauthors = Huber R, Langworthy TA, König H, Thomm M, Woese CR, Sleytr UB, Stetter KO  |year=1986 |title=''Thermotoga maritima'' sp. nov. represents a new genus of unique extremely thermophilic eubacteria growing up to 90°C |journal=[[Archives_of_Microbiology|Archives of Microbiology]] |volume=144 |issue=4 |pages=324–333 |doi=10.1007/BF00409880|s2cid=12709437 }}</ref>。

海栖热袍菌為厭氧的[[基本營養類型|化學自營]]生物，可將數種[[醣類|醣類]][[發酵|發酵]]產生[[二氧化碳|二氧化碳]]與[[氫氣|氫氣]]<ref name="MSU">{{cite web |publisher=[[蒙大拿州立大學|Montana State University]] |title=Geothermal organisms |access-date=January 14, 2012 |url=http://www.rcn.montana.edu/resources/organisms/organisminfo.aspx?nav=11&tid=1251&did=2&nid=2336&lid=9}}</ref><ref name=":3">{{cite journal | vauthors = Singh R, White D, Demirel Y, Kelly R, Noll K, Blum P | title = Uncoupling Fermentative Synthesis of Molecular Hydrogen from Biomass Formation in Thermotoga maritima | journal = Applied and Environmental Microbiology | volume = 84 | issue = 17 | date = September 2018 | pmid = 29959252 | pmc = 6102995 | doi = 10.1128/aem.00998-18 | bibcode = 2018ApEnM..84E.998S }}

</ref><ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Merrill AH, Lingrell S, Wang E, Nikolova-Karakashian M, Vales TR, Vance DE | title = Sphingolipid biosynthesis de novo by rat hepatocytes in culture. Ceramide and sphingomyelin are associated with, but not required for, very low density lipoprotein secretion | journal = The Journal of Biological Chemistry | volume = 270 | issue = 23 | pages = 13834–13841 | date = June 1995 | pmid = 7775441 | doi = 10.1074/jbc.270.23.13834 | doi-access = free }}</ref>。

